See Gemalto for current company information.Axalto was a smart card manufacturer with over 4,500 employees in 60 countries, one of the world's leading providers of microprocessor cards (Gartner, 2005) and also a major supplier of point of sale terminals.

In June 2006, Axalto merged with rival Gemplus International to form Gemalto.

Axalto's business covered the telecommunications, public telephony, finance, retail, transport, entertainment, healthcare, personal identification, information technology and public sector markets. The company recorded sales of over $992 million in 2005 and was fully-listed on Euronext, the pan-European market.



